covered: GET Method - Valid Request: Happy path with required path parameter and JSON array of Bundle objects is tested (TC01).
Pagination - Offset/Limit handling and resulting subset behavior (TC02, TC05) plus empty results when offset/limit exceed bounds (TC07, TC08).
Audit parameter handling - FULL and MINIMAL audit details in responses (TC03, TC04).
Query Parameter combinations - Various valid combinations including extra parameters (TC02, TC05, TC18).

Error Handling - Comprehensive coverage of 4xx and 5xx scenarios: invalid inputs (TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC17), authentication failures (TC13, TC14), service/unexpected errors (TC15, TC16), timeout (TC25).
Security Resilience - Injection attack scenario tested (TC17).
Performance/Scale Scenarios - Large data volume/response time expectations (TC19, TC20, TC25).
Data set variations - Empty database (TC24), partially populated database (TC23), and substring search (TC27).
Backward compatibility - Regression of prior valid parameter combinations (TC21).
Accessibility Consideration - UI accessibility scenario included (TC22).
gaps: Rate limiting/throttling behavior (e.g., 429) is not tested.
Caching behavior verification (ETag/Cache-Control headers) is not tested.
Authorization boundary lacking: test for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient permissions is not present.
Explicit last-page boundary and edge-case pagination with extremely large datasets beyond basic extremes is not tested (only very large offsets/limits).
Validation of edge-case path parameter formats beyond basic invalid/malformed input (e.g., extremely long or specially encoded strings) is not explicit.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests (429) to ensure proper throttling handling under bursty traffic.
Add caching header checks (ETag, Cache-Control) to verify caching behavior.
Include a 403 Forbidden scenario to cover insufficient-permission cases in addition to 401.
Add explicit last-page boundary tests and more granular pagination edge cases (e.g., end-of-list behavior with varying page sizes).
Augment input validation tests for extreme or edge-case searchKey inputs (very long strings, unusual encodings) to ensure robust validation.
